Question: The Nautilus development team shared requirements with the DevOps team regarding new application development.â€”specifically, they want to set up a Git repository for that project. Create a Git repository on Storage server in Stratos DC as per details given below:

Install git package using yum on Storage server.

After that create a bare repository /opt/media.git (make sure to use exact name).
login to storage server
ssh natasha@ststor01
then
yum install -y git
then
cd /opt/
git inti --bare media.git
git status
Click on Finish & Confirm to complete the task successful
